Curriculum progression logic is too aggressive.

The trainer is progressing into advanced flight tasks like WAYPOINT before the aircraft has truly mastered foundational flight skills.

This is incorrect.

============================================================
CURRENT PROBLEM
============================================================

The aircraft still:
- stalls frequently
- oscillates
- saturates controls
- lacks smooth stable flight

Yet curriculum already unlocks:
- waypoint
- advanced navigation

This contaminates PPO learning.

============================================================
REQUIRED FIX
============================================================

Curriculum progression must be MASTERY-BASED,
NOT timestep-based.

Do NOT unlock the next phase simply because enough timesteps elapsed.

============================================================
IMPLEMENT MASTERY GATES
============================================================

Only advance curriculum when current skill is truly stable.

============================================================
STABILIZE MASTERY REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Before unlocking ALTITUDE_HOLD:

Require ALL:

success_rate > 90%
crash_rate < 5%
stall_rate < 5%
mean_episode_length > threshold
mean_roll_rate < threshold
mean_pitch_rate < threshold
control_oscillation_metric low

Aircraft should visually:
- fly smoothly
- remain wings-level
- avoid stalls
- use small control inputs

============================================================
ALTITUDE HOLD MASTERY
============================================================

Before unlocking HDG_HOLD:

Require:
stable altitude tracking
low vertical oscillation
stable airspeed
low stall rate
smooth controls

============================================================
HEADING HOLD MASTERY
============================================================

Before unlocking WAYPOINT:

Require:
smooth coordinated turns
stable heading convergence
low bank oscillation
low stall rate during turns

============================================================
WAYPOINT MASTERY
============================================================

Before unlocking LOITER:
Require:
consistent waypoint interception
smooth path following
stable energy management

============================================================
APPROACH / LANDING
============================================================

Do NOT unlock approach or landing until:
core flight behavior is highly stable.

============================================================
IMPORTANT
============================================================

Foundational flight stabilization MUST become nearly automatic before introducing navigation complexity.

Otherwise PPO learns:
- unstable multitask compromise behavior
instead of:
- robust piloting skills.

============================================================
ADD CURRICULUM TELEMETRY
============================================================

Display:
- current curriculum phase
- mastery score
- unlock criteria
- which criteria still failing
- estimated readiness for next phase

Example:
STALL_RATE_TOO_HIGH
CONTROL_OSCILLATION_TOO_HIGH
ROLL_STABILITY_NOT_MET

============================================================
VISUALIZATION
============================================================

Add:
"NEXT PHASE LOCKED"

until mastery achieved.

============================================================
FINAL GOAL
============================================================

The UAV should learn:
1. stable flight
2. smooth energy management
3. coordinated turning
4. navigation
5. loiter
6. approach
7. landing

in that order.